<span id="freeTextContainer2721448799765217627">This collection of four little stories about Little Bear and his mother are quite cute. I can see why this book is still going strong half a century after it was first published.<br/><br/>I think my favourite story here is &quot;Little Bear Goes to the Moon&quot;. It&apos;s kind of silly, but in a gentle sort of way. Little Bear always has Mother Bear to come home to, even when he leaves the planet!<br/><br/>One thing I don&apos;t understand is why &quot;Birthday Soup&quot; is written in the present tense while the three other stories are in th</span>
  <span id="freeText2721448799765217627" style="display:none">This collection of four little stories about Little Bear and his mother are quite cute. I can see why this book is still going strong half a century after it was first published.<br><br>I think my favourite story here is "Little Bear Goes to the Moon". It's kind of silly, but in a gentle sort of way. Little Bear always has Mother Bear to come home to, even when he leaves the planet!<br><br>One thing I don't understand is why "Birthday Soup" is written in the present tense while the three other stories are in the past tense. That's probably my main complaint with this volume.<br><br>Overall, <i>Little Bear</i> is a charming storybook from a simpler time. It's held up well, despite being around since 1957!<br><br><b>Quotable moment:</b><br><br><blockquote>
  <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1558222436i/27538405.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</blockquote></span>
