<div id="review_394733167" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/394733167" />
    <a title="Andd Becker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11287861-andd-becker"><img alt="Andd Becker" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1380216403p2/11287861.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/394733167?book_show_action=true">Aug 18, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andd Becker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andd Becker" href="/user/show/11287861-andd-becker">Andd Becker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer394733167" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1663088988238100529">This is a perfect book. The four stories work well together, culminating in Mother Bear&apos;s reference to three of the stories.<br/> The illustrations by Maurice Sendak are outstanding.<br/> Mother Bear and Little Bear could be any mother and any child conversing about ordinary things such as what to wear; what to make on one&apos;s birthday; taking an imaginary trip to the moon; making wishes that will not come true (sit on cloud/fly; find Viking boat; find tunnel to China; go to a castle, in a big red car); and</span>
  <span id="freeText1663088988238100529" style="display:none">This is a perfect book. The four stories work well together, culminating in Mother Bear's reference to three of the stories.<br /> The illustrations by Maurice Sendak are outstanding.<br /> Mother Bear and Little Bear could be any mother and any child conversing about ordinary things such as what to wear; what to make on one's birthday; taking an imaginary trip to the moon; making wishes that will not come true (sit on cloud/fly; find Viking boat; find tunnel to China; go to a castle, in a big red car); and making a wish that will come true -- wishing that Mother Bear would tell a story to him.<br /> What happens next is what makes the book perfect: Mother Bear recounts three of the prior stories. Filled with the happy thought that Mother Bear did not forget his birthday, and remembering the birthday cake, Little Bear is in a receptive mood for Mother Bear's suggestion that he do what will make her happy -- go to sleep. Charming.<br /> Perfect.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1663088988238100529" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


